HEADWORD: Ill-judged
<hw>Ill"-judged`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not well judged;
unwise; not well considered or thought out; <as>as, an
<ex>ill-judged</ex> attempt</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ill-advised, ill considered, rash.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ill-lived</ent>⟦br⟧
